recipes.title: Classic Protein Brownies Recipe
recipes.description: These high-protein brownies are the perfect guilt-free indulgence, boasting an impressive 20g of muscle-repairing protein per serving to fuel your active lifestyle. Rich and fudgy, they offer a satisfying combination of moist, melt-in-your-mouth texture with a deep chocolate flavor that hits all the right notes. Whether you're craving a post-workout boost or a wholesome snack to power through your day, these brownies deliver both taste and nutrition in every bite. Their balanced macros make them suitable for those looking to support muscle growth or simply enjoy a healthier treat, and they can easily be adapted for gluten-free diets by using almond or coconut flour. For vegan options, substitute eggs with flaxseed or chia seed gel and choose plant-based protein powders. To get the best results, be sure not to overbake—removing them slightly undercooked ensures a gooey, decadent center. Perfect for meal prep, these brownies store well in the fridge and make a convenient, protein-packed snack whenever cravings strike.

instructions.text: Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C). Grease and line an 8x8 inch baking pan.
In a large bowl, whisk together the protein powder, almond flour, cocoa powder, sweetener, baking soda, and salt.
In a separate bowl, whisk together the eggs, applesauce, melted coconut oil, and vanilla extract.
Pour the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients and mix until just combined. Do not overmix.
Pour the batter into the prepared pan and spread evenly. Bake for 20-25 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out with moist crumbs.
Let the brownies cool completely in the pan before cutting into 12 squares.

instructions.text: Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C). Grease and line an 8x8 inch baking pan.

recipes.description: Shredded zucchini adds moisture and nutrients to these delicious protein brownies, making them a wholesome treat you can feel good about. With 16 grams of protein per serving, they’re perfect for supporting muscle recovery and keeping you energized throughout the day. The tender, fudgy texture combined with a subtle hint of sweetness creates a satisfying bite that melts in your mouth, while the zucchini imparts a gentle earthiness that balances the richness of the chocolate. These brownies are ideal as a post-workout snack, a healthy dessert, or even meal prep for busy weekdays; they stay moist and flavorful when stored in the fridge. They’re naturally gluten-free if you use gluten-free oats or flour, and vegan variations can be made with plant-based protein powders and egg substitutes. For best results, be sure to finely shred the zucchini and squeeze out excess moisture to prevent sogginess. A dash of sea salt or a sprinkle of cinnamon can elevate the flavor further, making these brownies irresistibly delicious while packing a serious nutritional punch.
ingredients: 150g shredded zucchini, squeezed of excess moisture

instructions.text: Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C). Grease an 8x8 inch baking pan.
Shred the zucchini and squeeze out as much moisture as possible with a clean kitchen towel.
In a large bowl, combine the shredded zucchini, eggs, protein powder, cocoa powder, oat flour, coconut sugar, melted coconut oil, and baking powder.
Stir until all ingredients are well combined.
Pour the batter into the prepared pan and bake for 28-30 minutes.
Let the brownies cool before slicing.

recipes.title: Peanut Butter Protein Brownies
recipes.description: This indulgent high-protein brownie combines rich chocolate with creamy peanut butter for a flavor explosion that satisfies your sweet cravings while fueling your body. Packed with 22 grams of protein per serving, it's an ideal choice for post-workout recovery or a nutritious snack to keep you energized throughout the day. The fudgy texture melts in your mouth, offering a perfect balance of moistness and density, with a decadent chocolate-peanut butter flavor that’s both indulgent and satisfying. Each bite provides a wholesome boost of macros, making it easy to stay on track with your fitness goals without sacrificing flavor. These brownies are versatile and can be enjoyed as a quick breakfast, a pre- or post-workout treat, or even meal prep for the week ahead. For those with dietary restrictions, they can easily be made gluten-free with your favorite gluten-free flour, and vegan options are simple by swapping in plant-based protein powder and nut butters. For best results, use high-quality cocoa and natural peanut butter, and avoid overmixing to keep the brownies tender. Chill them slightly before serving to enhance their fudgy consistency, and enjoy a guilt-free indulgence that’s as nutritious as it is delicious.

instructions.text: Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C). Grease an 8x8 inch baking pan.
In a large bowl, whisk together the protein powder, peanut butter powder, cocoa powder, and sweetener.
In a separate bowl, whisk the eggs, Greek yogurt, and creamy peanut butter until smooth.
Pour the wet ingredients into the dry and mix until a thick batter forms.
Spread the batter into the prepared pan. Optional: swirl in extra peanut butter on top. Bake for 22-25 minutes.
Let the brownies cool completely before slicing.

recipes.title: Mint Chocolate Protein Brownies
recipes.description: This refreshing and delicious mint chocolate protein brownie packs a satisfying 20g of muscle-nourishing protein per serving, making it the perfect treat to fuel your day. With a rich, fudgy texture complemented by a hint of cool mint, each bite offers a delightful balance of deep chocolate flavor and invigorating freshness that keeps cravings at bay. Crafted with wholesome ingredients, these brownies are not only indulgent but also support your fitness goals by providing balanced macros—low in sugar and calories, yet high in protein and healthy fats. Their moist, chewy consistency makes them ideal for post-workout recovery or as a satisfying snack anytime you need a boost. For those with dietary restrictions, you can easily adapt this recipe to be gluten-free by using almond or coconut flour, and vegan options are simple with plant-based protein powders and dairy-free chocolate. For best results, be sure to measure ingredients precisely and avoid overbaking, which can dry out the brownies. Store them in an airtight container for a quick, nutritious treat that’s perfect for meal prep or sharing with friends.

instructions.text: Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C). Grease and line an 8x8 inch baking pan.
In a large bowl, whisk together the protein powder, almond flour, cocoa powder, and sweetener.
In a separate bowl, whisk together the eggs, applesauce, melted coconut oil, and peppermint extract.
Pour the wet ingredients into the dry and mix until just combined.
Pour the batter into the prepared pan and bake for 22-25 minutes.
Let the brownies cool completely before slicing.

recipes.title: Raspberry Swirl Protein Brownies
recipes.description: Indulge in these fudgy chocolate protein brownies with a stunning and flavorful raspberry swirl, offering an irresistible combination of rich cocoa and vibrant fruitiness. Packed with 19 grams of high-quality protein per serving, they’re perfect for satisfying your sweet tooth while supporting muscle recovery and overall nutrition. The dense, moist texture melts in your mouth, with a deep chocolate flavor balanced by the tangy burst of raspberry, creating a delightful contrast that keeps every bite exciting. Ideal for post-workout refueling or a nutritious snack, these brownies also make excellent meal prep options—simply store and enjoy whenever craving something sweet and nourishing. They can easily be adapted for gluten-free diets by using almond or coconut flour, and vegan versions can be made with plant-based protein powder and dairy-free chocolate. For best results, use ripe raspberries for a vibrant swirl and gently fold the fruit into the batter to achieve a beautiful marbled effect. Whether you’re aiming to boost your macros or enjoy a decadent yet healthy treat, these brownies are sure to become a favorite in your fitness-focused kitchen.

instructions.text: Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C). Grease an 8x8 inch baking pan.
In a large bowl, whisk together the protein powder, oat flour, cocoa powder, sweetener, baking soda, eggs, and Greek yogurt until a thick batter forms.
Pour the brownie batter into the prepared pan and spread evenly.
Dollop the mashed raspberries over the top of the batter. Use a knife to gently swirl the raspberries into the brownie batter.
Bake for 25-28 minutes, or until the center is set.
Let the brownies cool completely before slicing.

recipes.title: Espresso Protein Brownies
recipes.description: These rich and fudgy protein brownies are the perfect indulgence for anyone looking to satisfy their sweet tooth while fueling their body. Packed with 20 grams of high-quality protein per serving, they provide a satisfying boost to support muscle recovery and keep you energized throughout the day. The deep, chocolatey flavor is enhanced by a bold kick of espresso, creating a luxurious, velvety texture that melts in your mouth with each bite. The dense, chewy consistency makes them ideal for a post-workout treat or a nutritious snack to keep hunger at bay. Thanks to their balanced macros and wholesome ingredients, they can easily be incorporated into meal prep routines for a quick grab-and-go option. For those with dietary restrictions, these brownies can be made gluten-free using almond or coconut flour, and vegan versions are simple with plant-based protein and dairy-free chocolate. For best results, be sure not to overbake; remove them from the oven when a toothpick inserted in the center comes out slightly moist to maintain that irresistibly fudgy texture. Enjoy them warm for a decadent experience or store them in an airtight container for an easy, protein-packed treat anytime you need a delicious pick-me-up.

instructions.text: Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C). Grease and line an 8x8 inch baking pan.
In a large bowl, whisk together the protein powder, almond flour, cocoa powder, sweetener, espresso powder, and baking soda.
In a separate bowl, whisk together the eggs, applesauce, and melted coconut oil.
Pour the wet ingredients into the dry and mix until just combined.
Pour the batter into the prepared pan and bake for 22-25 minutes.
Let the brownies cool completely before slicing.

recipes.title: Gluten-Free Black Bean Protein Brownies
recipes.description: Fudgy, rich brownies made with black beans for a naturally gluten-free base. You won't believe these decadent treats are packed with protein and fiber! Each serving offers around 12 grams of muscle-repairing protein and a generous dose of dietary fiber, making them an excellent choice for fueling post-workout recovery or satisfying your sweet tooth healthfully. The dense, melt-in-your-mouth texture is complemented by deep chocolate flavor with just a hint of earthiness from the beans, creating a perfectly balanced, indulgent bite. These brownies are ideal for meal prep, as they stay moist and tasty for days, allowing you to enjoy a nutritious treat anytime. They're naturally gluten-free, and vegan options are easily achieved by substituting eggs with flaxseed or chia seed gel. For best results, blend the beans thoroughly to ensure a smooth batter and avoid overbaking to maintain that fudgy consistency. Whether you're craving a guilt-free dessert or a high-protein snack, these brownies are a delicious way to nourish your body without sacrificing flavor.
ingredients: 400g canned black beans, drained and rinsed

instructions.text: Preheat oven to 175°C (350°F). Line an 8x8 inch baking pan with parchment paper.
Add black beans, eggs, maple syrup, nut butter, and vanilla to a food processor. Blend until completely smooth.
Add the protein powder, cocoa powder, baking powder, and salt. Blend until combined.
Fold in the chocolate chips. Pour batter into the prepared pan and spread evenly.
Bake for 22-25 minutes until set but still slightly fudgy in the center. Cool completely before cutting into 12 brownies.

recipes.title: Dairy-Free Avocado Protein Brownies
recipes.description: These ultra-fudgy dairy-free brownies are a guilt-free indulgence packed with nutritious goodness, delivering approximately 10 grams of protein per serving to fuel your body and satisfy your sweet cravings. Made with creamy avocado, they boast healthy fats that contribute to sustained energy and skin nourishment, all while providing a decadent, melt-in-your-mouth texture that’s rich and velvety. The intense chocolate flavor is perfectly balanced by the smooth, moist crumb, making each bite irresistibly luscious. Thanks to the wholesome ingredients and lack of dairy, they're suitable for vegan and gluten-free diets—just ensure you use gluten-free oats or flour if needed. These brownies are ideal for post-workout recovery or as a nutritious snack on busy days, and they store beautifully for meal prep, offering a quick sweet fix whenever cravings strike. For best results, underbake slightly to keep the center fudgy and moist, and consider adding a sprinkle of sea salt or dairy-free chocolate chips on top for extra flavor. Whether enjoyed with a glass of plant-based milk or on their own, these brownies are a satisfying, health-conscious treat you’ll want to keep on hand!
ingredients: 2 flax eggs (2 tbsp ground flaxseed + 6 tbsp water)

instructions.text: Mix ground flaxseed with water and let sit for 5 minutes until gel-like.
In a food processor, blend the avocado until completely smooth with no lumps.
Add the coconut sugar, almond milk, flax eggs, and vanilla to the avocado. Blend until smooth.
Add protein powder, cocoa powder, baking soda, and salt. Blend until combined. Fold in chocolate chips.
Pour into a parchment-lined 8x8 pan. Bake at 175°C (350°F) for 22-25 minutes. Cool completely before slicing.
